# CLAUDE.md — Rules for Claude Code (v5)

## Context
This project uses the **ai-spec-driven-generator** framework v5 (in `framework/`).
You must follow a structured, phase-based process with human validation,
persistent memory, and machine-verifiable acceptance criteria.

**Start here if you want the minimum briefing**:
- `framework/rules/CHEATSHEET.md` — 1-page TL;DR (commands, top-10 rules, gates, exit codes)
- `framework/rules/GUIDE.md` — full rules (principles, coding standards, test quality, agent conduct, commits, git flow)
- `framework/_docs/PIPELINE.md` — the whole pipeline (commands, gates, agents, scripts, state machine)

## Fundamental principles

| Principle | Rule |
|-----------|------|
| **Agnostic** | Core framework is Python + YAML. Stack-awareness lives in `_work/stacks/`. Four built-in stacks: `python-fastapi`, `typescript-react`, `postgres`, `nodejs-express`. Projects can add custom stacks — see `framework/stacks/CUSTOM_STACK_GUIDE.md`. Check `spec.type` before applying platform-specific rules. |
| **Autonomous** | Humans decide (product, UX, architecture, go-live). Machines verify (tests, quality, security, perf). Auto-proceed when gates pass. Escalation after 3 failed cycles is **blocking** — only `/resume <story-id> "reason"` clears it. |
| **Accompaniment** | `/help`, `/status`, `/next`, `/resume` and unified messages (`framework/scripts/ui_messages.py`) keep the user in the loop. No silent execution. Respond in the user's language. |

## Commands in v5

Tape `/next` quand tu arrives le matin — le framework te dit quoi faire.

| Skill | What it does |
|---|---|
| `/spec` | Define a new project (constitution, scope, UX, architecture). |
| `/ux <feature>` | UX design — IA, flows, wireframes, DS tokens (UI projects). |
| `/refine <feature>` | Break feature into stories with `verify:` + oracle values. |
| `/build <story-id>` | Orchestrator: auto-dispatch builder, TDD RED→GREEN, run gates. |
| `/validate <story-id>` | Read-only rerun of gates on current repo. |
| `/review [story-id\|--all]` | Read-only audit — PASS/FAIL verdict. Never creates PR. |
| `/ship <story-id>` | **Single exit** — runs `/review`; on PASS pushes + opens PR with `sdd-validated-v5` tag. |
| `/scan [--full] [--report]` | SonarQube / semgrep / eslint scan. |
| `/next [--scope …] [--json]` | Prioritised action list (BLOCKING / IN-PROGRESS / READY / PENDING SHIP / SUGGESTIONS). |
| `/status [story-id]` | Dashboard view — stats, gates, escalations, history. |
| `/help [command]` | Contextual help. |
| `/resume <story-id> "reason"` | Unlock an escalated/tampered story (reason mandatory). |
| `/migrate [--to VERSION]` | Run migration scripts. |

**Default workflow**: `/spec` → `/refine` → `/build` → `/ship` (per story).
`/validate` and `/review` are audit-only intermediate steps.

## Loading agents (important)

v5 has **18 agents** in `framework/agents/`. Skills load only what they need —
never load all agents at once. Each agent file declares its `model:` in YAML
frontmatter; pass that model when spawning the subagent.

- If the agent frontmatter says `model: opus` → spawn with `model: "opus"`
- If the agent frontmatter says `model: sonnet` → spawn with `model: "sonnet"`
- If no `model:` field → use the current session model
- To override per project, see `§Agent model overrides` at the bottom.

## Gates G1–G14

v5 uses unified gate numbering adaptive per `spec.type`. Only applicable gates
run — the rest are absent from the log (not "skipped"). See
`framework/rules/CHEATSHEET.md` for one-liner table and
`framework/_docs/PIPELINE.md` for the full reference.

Core gates (all types): G1 Security · G2 Unit tests · G2.1 Mutation · G2.2
Regression · G2.3 Contract diff · G3 Code quality · G4 Build · G4.1 Smoke boot ·
G5 AC mechanical · G6 Story review · G7 Code review · G8 Integration cross-stories.

Conditional gates: G9.1–G9.6 (web-ui/mobile) · G10 Performance · G11
Observability (web-api/web-ui/ml-pipeline) · G12 DAST-lite (web-api/web-ui) ·
G13 Migration safety · G14 Release readiness (at `/ship`).

## Enforcement scripts (20)

All in `framework/scripts/`. The orchestrator runs them; git hooks
(`scripts/setup-hooks.sh`) give feedback. Every `--no-verify` is detected at the
next orchestrator pass and moves the story to `status: tampered`.

Script categories: 6 refactored in v5 (AST) + 4 retained + 10 new (interaction
tests, visual regression, behavioral regression, observability, performance
budget, release artifacts, migration safety, contract diff, DS conformity,
integration coverage).

Full list: `framework/_docs/PIPELINE.md §5`.

## On session start

### New project (no memory file exists)
1. Tell the user: "We'll define your project together before writing any code.
   I'll guide you through Constitution → Scope → Clarify → UX → Architecture
   → then we build."
2. Launch `/spec`.
3. After `/spec`: launch `/refine` for the first feature.
4. Only then: `/build <story-id>` for each refined story, ending each with `/ship`.

**NEVER jump to code.** Always start with `/spec`.

### Existing project (memory file exists)
1. Read `memory/<project-name>.md` to restore context.
2. Read `memory/LESSONS.md` for known pitfalls.
3. Read `specs/feature-tracker.yaml` to know feature states.
4. Run `/next` — summarise BLOCKING + IN-PROGRESS items to the user.
5. Resume with the appropriate skill.

## Phase workflow

```
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
PHASE 0 — CONCEPTION (/spec) — Human validation at each step
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Constitution → specs/constitution.md
  Scoping (PO) → specs/<project>.yaml
  Clarify      → specs/<project>-clarifications.md
  UX/UI        → specs/<project>-ux.md (web-ui/mobile)
  Architecture → specs/<project>-arch.md
  Tracker init → specs/feature-tracker.yaml

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
PHASE 1 — CONSTRUCTION (per story loop) — Auto
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  /refine <feature> → story file + manifest + oracle values → ✅ Human validation
  /build <story-id> → Orchestrator runs TDD RED→GREEN + gates G1..G14
                   → /validate is optional audit during build cycles
                   → PASS: status = validated (no PR yet)
                   → FAIL: cycle ≤ 3, then status = escalated

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
PHASE 2 — SHIP (/ship) — Single exit
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  /ship <story-id> runs /review internally on the full branch.
    PASS → push + gh pr create + tag `sdd-validated-v5`
    FAIL → no PR, detailed report

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
PHASE 3 — DEPLOY / RELEASE — ✅ Human
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
```

## Phase guards

Before executing a skill, verify prerequisites on the filesystem:

| Skill | Prerequisites | If missing |
|---|---|---|
| `/spec` | None — this is the starting point | — |
| `/refine` | `specs/<project>.yaml` + `specs/<project>-arch.md` + `specs/feature-tracker.yaml` | → "Let's define the project first" → `/spec` |
| `/build` | `specs/stories/<id>.yaml` + feature status=`refined` | → "Story needs refinement" → `/refine` |
| `/validate` | Feature status=`building` or `validated` | → "Nothing to validate yet" → `/build` |
| `/review` | At least one feature in `validated` state | → list features not ready |
| `/ship` | Feature status=`validated` | → "Run /build first" |
| `/resume` | Feature status=`escalated` or `tampered` + `reason` argument | → "Reason is mandatory" |

## Feature tracker states

| State | Meaning | Set by |
|---|---|---|
| `pending` | Declared in spec, not refined | `/spec` |
| `refined` | Story file + manifest + oracle values written | `/refine` |
| `building` | `/build` running or cycling | `/build` |
| `validated` | All applicable gates passed | `/build` on PASS |
| `shipped` | PR created with `sdd-validated-v5` tag | `/ship` |
| `escalated` | Max cycles, requires `/resume` | `/build` (terminal) |
| `tampered` | Bypass detected, requires `/resume` | Any tamper check (terminal) |

## Acceptance criteria format (unified)

**ONE format** — spec, story files, validation reports:

```yaml
acceptance_criteria:
  - id: "AC-FUNC-AUTH-01"              # AC-<TYPE>-<FEATURE>-<NUMBER>
    type: "FUNC"                       # FUNC | SEC | BP | UX
    description: "Given a valid email and password / When user submits / Then session created"
    verify: "curl -s -o /dev/null -w '%{http_code}' -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login -d '{\"email\":\"test@test.com\",\"password\":\"pass\"}'"
    tier: 2                            # 1 (grep/bash) | 2 (curl/playwright) | 3 (runtime)
```

- `verify: static` is **banned** — rewrite until you have a shell command.
- AC-SEC-* must be Tier 1 (code artefacts, not runtime).
- No AC without `verify:`.

## Git flow (summary — full rules in GUIDE.md §6)

| Branch | Role |
|---|---|
| `main` | Production only (release PRs) |
| `develop` | Integration — feature PRs target here |
| `feat/*` | One per feature, branched from `origin/develop` |

All PRs target the integration branch. `/ship` is the only way to create a PR.
Manually-created PRs lack the `sdd-validated-v5` tag and are rejected at human
review.

Unrelated work goes in a `.worktrees/` worktree branched from `origin/develop`.

## Strict rules (see GUIDE.md §7 for the full list)

1. Always read memory at session start.
2. Always update tracker + memory at state transitions.
3. Always follow phase order (filesystem enforces it).
4. Never load all agents — skills load what they need.
5. Never code before conception phases are complete.
6. Never skip `verify:` commands.
7. Always run enforcement scripts before commits.
8. Never assert computed values without ORACLE.
9. Never skip a `test_intention` from the spec.
10. Never `git add .` / `git add -A`.
11. Never mix branches — unrelated work goes in a worktree.
12. All PRs target the integration branch (never `main` except releases).
13. **`/ship` is the only way out** — never `gh pr create` manually.

